4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) There is hereby established an Office of Election Investigations and Security
6 within the Office of the Attorney General, which shall:
7 (a) Respond to notifications or complaints generated by election officials or any
8 other person alleging a violation of the state election law;
9 (b) Review notices and reports of an alleged violation of the state election law
10 and conduct investigations of any incidents that it determines require
11 further investigation;
12 (c) Initiate independent inquiries or conduct preliminary investigations into
13 any alleged violation of the state election law in any jurisdiction of this state
14 that it determines requires investigation;
15 (d) Employ investigators to conduct any investigations;
16 (e) Oversee the voter fraud hotline; and
17 (f) For purposes of investigation, have the authority to receive sworn
18 statements and issue subpoenas to compel the production of records and
19 other documents.
20 (2) If the office determines there may be a violation of any criminal law or state
21 election law, it shall inform the Attorney General or refer the findings of its
22 investigation to the appropriate Commonwealth's or county attorney for further
23 investigation or prosecution.
24 (3) The office shall submit a report by July 1 of each year to the Legislative Research
25 Commission, which provides detailed information on investigations of alleged
26 violations of the state election laws during the prior calendar year and includes:
27 (a) The total number of complaints received, independent investigations
